[asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F;

B = (0,0);
C = (1,0);
A = extension(B, B + dir(60), C, C + dir(60));
D = (B + C)/3;
E = (2*B + C)/3;
F = (B + C)/2;

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--F);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$E$", E, S);
label("$F$", F, S);
[/asy]

Since $\triangle ADF$ is a 30-60-90 triangle, $AF = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} DF = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{8} BC.$  Then
\[AE = \sqrt{AF^2 + EF^2} = \sqrt{\frac{3}{64} BC^2 + \frac{1}{16} BC^2} = \frac{\sqrt{7}}{8} BC.\]Also, $AD = \frac{3}{4} BC,$ so
\[\sin \angle DAE = \frac{DE}{AD} = \frac{BC/3}{3BC/4} = \boxed{\frac{4}{9}}.\]

